Dialogue: 5,0:00:53.58,0:00:58.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The path I take there, the path I take home
Dialogue: 5,0:00:58.59,0:01:04.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On this bridge that seems like it goes on forever
Dialogue: 5,0:01:04.26,0:01:09.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I could cross over it, if I forget about it
Dialogue: 5,0:01:09.13,0:01:14.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I could go off towards some distant unknown place
Dialogue: 5,0:01:14.59,0:01:19.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It’s somebody’s fault, it’s for somebody’s sake
Dialogue: 5,0:01:19.93,0:01:25.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Over and over, you shrug it off and say,
Dialogue: 5,0:01:25.23,0:01:30.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Throwing yesterday away, as if you’ve given up on tomorrow
Dialogue: 5,0:01:30.94,0:01:36.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I close my eyelids again, and see inside them
Dialogue: 5,0:01:36.47,0:01:40.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those pieces of you, shattered into a million colors
Dialogue: 5,0:01:40.95,0:01:47.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just like the stars above, sparkled over and over again
Dialogue: 5,0:01:47.27,0:01:53.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They faded into a million-colored monochrome
Dialogue: 5,0:01:53.27,0:01:59.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That dream I once saw
Dialogue: 5,0:01:59.96,0:02:07.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even now, I line it up on my palette as I paint
Dialogue: 5,0:02:07.93,0:02:17.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The everything of this blank and brilliant world
Dialogue: 5,0:02:26.90,0:02:31.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The passing rain, the sudden rain
Dialogue: 5,0:02:31.94,0:02:37.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When did it start falling upon this bridge?
Dialogue: 5,0:02:37.55,0:02:42.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I could go back, if I can bring myself to recall
Dialogue: 5,0:02:42.59,0:02:47.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How you held out that umbrella, and something else important
Dialogue: 5,0:02:47.78,0:02:53.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I tried to gaze up at the sky, tried to think of somebody
Dialogue: 5,0:02:53.23,0:02:58.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Over and over, and then I cast my eyes down
Dialogue: 5,0:02:58.58,0:03:04.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something a bit like pain seems to have been left faintly behind
Dialogue: 5,0:03:04.57,0:03:09.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the palm of my clenched hand
Dialogue: 5,0:03:09.89,0:03:14.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those pieces of you, broken into a million colors
Dialogue: 5,0:03:14.27,0:03:20.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just like fine sand, slips between my fingers
Dialogue: 5,0:03:20.57,0:03:26.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They were colored with a million-colored monochrome
Dialogue: 5,0:03:26.57,0:03:33.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The meaning of your living
Dialogue: 5,0:03:33.22,0:03:41.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even now, I continue to paint on my canvas
Dialogue: 5,0:03:41.27,0:03:52.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The everything of this blank and brilliant world
Dialogue: 5,0:04:32.50,0:04:36.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those pieces of you, shattered into a million colors
Dialogue: 5,0:04:36.93,0:04:43.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just like the stars above, sparkled over and over again
Dialogue: 5,0:04:43.21,0:04:51.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And were colored with a million-colored monochrome
Dialogue: 5,0:04:51.03,0:04:55.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those pieces of you, broken into a million colors
